From: Dan Rosenberg <dan.j.rosenberg@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Sep 2010 10:41:32 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] xfs: prevent reading uninitialized stack memory

Commit a122eb2fdfd78b58c6dd992d6f4b1aaef667eef9 from upstream.

The XFS_IOC_FSGETXATTR ioctl allows unprivileged users to read 12
bytes of uninitialized stack memory, because the fsxattr struct
declared on the stack in xfs_ioc_fsgetxattr() does not alter (or zero)
the 12-byte fsx_pad member before copying it back to the user.  This
patch takes care of it.

Signed-off-by: Dan Rosenberg <dan.j.rosenberg@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Eric Sandeen <sandeen@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Elder <aelder@sgi.com>
Integrated-by:  Shenbo Huang<shenbo.huang@windriver.com>
---
 fs/xfs/linux-2.6/xfs_ioctl.c |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fs/xfs/linux-2.6/xfs_ioctl.c b/fs/xfs/linux-2.6/xfs_ioctl.c
index 48799ba..ab1a2d8 100644
--- a/fs/xfs/linux-2.6/xfs_ioctl.c
+++ b/fs/xfs/linux-2.6/xfs_ioctl.c
@@ -853,6 +853,8 @@ xfs_ioc_fsgetxattr(
 {
 	struct fsxattr		fa;
 
+	memset(&fa, 0, sizeof(struct fsxattr));
+
 	xfs_ilock(ip, XFS_ILOCK_SHARED);
 	fa.fsx_xflags = xfs_ip2xflags(ip);
 	fa.fsx_extsize = ip->i_d.di_extsize << ip->i_mount->m_sb.sb_blocklog;
